e\nformation cross-section of daughter species, and the half-life of the parental\nspecies in a simulated Enceladus irradiation scenario were determined. Among\nthe produced species, CO (carbon monoxide), OCN- (cyanate anion), HCONH2\n(formamide), and H2CO (formaldehyde) were tentatively detected.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 3 Nov 2014 16:43:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-11-04"}
