axies' half-mass radii\nby a factor of a few to below 2 kpc, and (ii) assembly at very early times when\nthe universe was much denser; the galaxies formed compact and remained so until\nz~2.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 3 Nov 2014 21:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 6 Nov 2014 19:13:41 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 17 Feb 2015 23:29:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
